messages.content: ComfyUI-SeeCoder is a set of ComfyUI nodes that allow the use of the SeeCoder model from the Prompt-Free-Diffusion project.
Where can I find the Prompt-Free-Diffusion models?
The Prompt-Free-Diffusion models can be found on Huggingface at https://huggingface.co/shi-labs/prompt-free-diffusion/tree/main/pretrained/pfd/seecoder.
Which Prompt-Free-Diffusion model works best for all use cases?
The anime model from Prompt-Free-Diffusion tends to work best for all use cases.
Where should I download the Prompt-Free-Diffusion models?
The Prompt-Free-Diffusion models should be downloaded to the `ComfyUI/models/seecoder/` directory.
Are there any additional resources to improve the quality of generations?

Yes, you can use the specific unconditional provided by the original Prompt-Free-Diffusion repo from https://github.com/SHI-Labs/Prompt-Free-Diffusion/tree/master/assets. These are optional but can improve the quality of the generation.
Where should I download the additional unconditional resources?
The additional unconditional resources should also be downloaded to the `ComfyUI/models/seecoder/` directory.
Where can I find examples of using ComfyUI-SeeCoder?
Examples of using ComfyUI-SeeCoder can be found in the `example_workflows` directory.
